Introduction¶

This dataset collects information from 100k medical appointments in Brazil and is focused on the question of whether or not patients show up for their appointment. A number of characteristics about the patient are included in each row.

‘ScheduledDay’ tells us on what day the patient set up their appointment.
‘Neighborhood’ indicates the location of the hospital.
‘Scholarship’ indicates whether or not the patient is enrolled in Brasilian welfare program Bolsa Família.

In [55]:
def attendance(df,column,show,no_show):
    plt.figure(figsize=[20,10]);
    df[column][show].value_counts().plot(kind='bar',color='green',label='Attend'); 
    df[column][no_show].value_counts().plot(kind='bar',color='yellow',label='Absent');
    plt.legend();
    plt.title(column +' influencing attendance');
    plt.xlabel(column);
    plt.ylabel('Patients Number');
attendance(df,'Gender',attend,absent)    
pd.DataFrame(df['Gender'][attend].value_counts())
Out[55]:
Gender
F 34914
M 19143

there is no clear relation between the show status and the gender

Question 2(is patient age influence the show status¶

In [51]:
#grouping age for show status to get if there relation between the age and show status

def attendance_hist(df,column,show,no_show):
    plt.figure(figsize=[20,10]);
    df[column][show].hist(alpha=.5,bins=10,color='green',label='Attend');
    df[column][no_show].hist(alpha=.5,bins=10,color='yellow',label='Absent');
    plt.legend();
    plt.title(column + 'influencing attendance');
    plt.xlabel(column);
    plt.ylabel('Patient Number');
attendance_hist(df,'Age',attend,absent)    
pd.DataFrame(df.groupby(['No_show'])['Age'].value_counts())

conclusions¶

  • Most of patients are not included in the scholarship
  • there is relation between age of patients and attendance as the most attendees age range from 0(infants) to 10 , The second raise in attendence is for patients from 45 to 57 years old while the least attendees are patients from 80 to over 100 years old
  • The neibourhood with max number of attendees is JARDIM CAMBURI and the neibourhood with min attendees is (PARQUE INDUSTRIAL) neighbourhood has a greet effect on attendance
  • patients who did not received SMS attended their appointments more than patients received the SMS which mean we need to review our SMS targeting strategy
  • Number of attended patients from specific neighbourhood is affected by receiving SMS snd Age

Limitations:¶

  • there is no clear relation between the show status and the gender
  • Alcoholism is not affect attendance
  • Handicap is not affect attendance
  • Normal patient attendace is the most percentile,although when comparing patient with cronic disease who attend vs who absent we will find that attendees with chronic disease is more than absent patient with chronic diseases aprox. 3 times so chronic disease doesnot affect attendance
  • Majority of attendees doesn't have a scholarship, so scholarship does not has clear effect on the attendance
  • No correlation between age and gender affecting the attendance
